pull_request.title: Update list of releases and supported algorithms
Bump _includes/liboqs from `a5ec23c` to `4cc8884`
pull_request.body:
Bumps [_includes/liboqs](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs) from `a5ec23c` to `4cc8884`.
Commits
  • 4cc8884 Add MAYO signature scheme from NIST onramp (#1707)
  • 26feef2 Expose callback API for replacing low-level cryptographic primitives (#1832)
  • d2089c5 Add OpenSSF scorecard
  • 51ddd33 Add XMSS-SHAKE256_{10, 16, 20}_256 parameters (#1819)
  • e3f05cb add XMSS-SHAKE256_*_192 parameters (#1818)
  • 5e31116 Add XMSS-SHA256_{10, 16, 20}_192 parameters (#1817)
  • 21ab593 Increment version [skip ci] (#1813)
  • c8a2beb Fix test_alg_info.py on Windows platform (#1821)
  • 6ee5de2 Move Linux ARM64 "build" test from CircleCI to GitHub Actions (#1814)
  • 39688e9 Forward-declare OQS_SIG type in sig_stfl.h (#1820)
  • Additional commits viewable in compare view

Dependabot will resolve any conflicts with this PR as long as you don't alter it yourself. You can also trigger a rebase manually by commenting `@dependabot rebase`. [//]: # (dependabot-automerge-start) [//]: # (dependabot-automerge-end) ---

You can achieve the same result by closing it manually - `@dependabot show ignore conditions` will show all of the ignore conditions of the specified dependency - `@dependabot ignore this major version` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this major version (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself) - `@dependabot ignore this minor version` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this minor version (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself) - `@dependabot ignore this dependency` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this dependency (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself)

pull_request.title: Update list of releases and supported algorithms
Update and fix CI status badges
pull_request.body:
This PR updates and fixes the CI status badges in the README.

Changes made:

1. Removed redundant text labels preceding the badges.
2. Corrected the broken Travis CI badge and URL and switched to shields.io for the badge to include the logo.
3. Updated the CircleCI badge to use the shield style for visual consistency with the other badge.

Note: This is a purely cosmetic change to the markdown file. It does not add new features, affect input/output behavior, or alter the list of algorithms. No version bump or downstream project updates are required.
